{{no footnotes|date=August 2012}} {{use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Aargauer Zeitung | logo = Aargauer Zeitung.svg | image = | caption = | type = [[Daily newspaper]] | format = | owners = [[AZ Medien Gruppe]] | founder = | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | seniorstaff = | staff = | foundation = 1996 | political = | language = [[German language|German]] | headquarters = [[Aarau]], [[Aargau]], [[Switzerland]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = 611044404 | website = [http://www.aargauerzeitung.ch aargauerzeitung.ch] (in [[German language|German]]) }}
'''''Aargauer Zeitung''''' (English: ''Aargauer Newspaper'') is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[German language|German-language]] [[daily newspaper]], published by [[AZ Medien Gruppe]], [[Aarau]], [[Aargau]].
==History and operations== [[Image:Picswiss AG-26-22.jpg|thumb|''Aargauer Zeitung'''s building in [[Aarau]].]]
''Aagauer Zeitung'' was created in 1996 through the merger of the ''[[Aargauer Tagblatt (newspaper)|Aargauer Tagblatt]]'' and ''[[Badener Tagblatt (newspaper)|Badener Tagblatt]]'' newspapers.<!--at august 2012, intentionally added "(newspaper)" and piped link to avoid self redirect. predecessor newspapers have a history and future-article potential--> The paper is edited in Aarau and [[Baden, Switzerland|Baden]], Aargau. It produces several local editions, including under the titles ''Zofinger Tagblatt'' and ''Limmattaler Tagblatt''.<!--not linked at august 2012, future-article potential seems slim-->
Since January 2002, ''[[Mittelland Zeitung]]'' has been the common, core section of the newspaper as well as for newspapers ''[[Oltner Tagblatt]]'' and ''[[Solothurner Zeitung]]'' with a circulation of 200,000.{{when|date=August 2012}}
In 1997 ''Aargauer Zeitung'' had a circulation of 118,578 copies.<ref> {{cite journal |author = Sibylle Hardmeier |title = Political Poll Reporting in Swiss Print Media |journal = International Journal of Public Opinion Research |date = 1999 |volume = 11 |issue = 3 |url = http://ijpor.oxfordjournals.org/content/11/3/257.full.pdf |accessdate = 30 December 2014 |ref = harv}}</ref>
