'''''The Brethren''''' (in Czech language '''''Bratrstvo''''') is a [[Czech language|Czech]] novel trilogy, written by [[Alois Jirásek]]. The main characters of book are Czech warlords [[John Jiskra of Brandýs]] and John Talafus, who fought in present-day [[Slovakia]] against Hungarian duke [[John Hunyadi]].

