{{Infobox building |name = Le Bahia |image = |location = 39, Avenue Princesse Grace, Larvotto, Monaco |coordinates = |status = Complete |start_date = |completion_date = 1971 |building_type = |architectural_style = Modernist |roof = |floor_count = 12 |elevator_count = |cost = |floor_area = |architect = |structural_engineer= |main_contractor = |developer = |owner = [[Hélène Pastor]] <small>(formerly)</small> |management = |references = }} '''Le Bahia''' is a high-rise residential building in [[Monaco]].
==Location== It is located at 39 [[Avenue Princesse Grace]] in the [[Larvotto]] district of [[Monaco]].<ref name="emporislebahia">[http://www.emporis.com/building/le-bahia-monaco-monaco Le Bahia], [[Emporis]]</ref><ref name="structurae">[http://structurae.net/structures/le-bahia Le Bahia], [[Structurae]]</ref><ref name="helene">[http://www.hpp.mc/groupe.html Hélène Pastor Pallanca: Le Bahia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150127084202/http://www.hpp.mc/groupe.html |date=2015-01-27 }}</ref>
==History== The construction of the building was completed in 1971.<ref name="structurae"/> It was built by the Monegasque construction firm, [[J. B. Pastor et fils]].<ref>[http://jbpastoretfils.mc/?page_id=727&lang=en J. B. Pastor et fils: History]</ref> It was designed in the [[modernist architecture|modernist]] architectural style.<ref name="emporislebahia"/> It is 38.35 metres high, with twelve storeys.<ref name="emporislebahia"/>
It was owned by heiress [[Hélène Pastor]] through her eponymous real estate company.<ref name="helene"/><ref name="bloombergtom">Tom Metcalf, [https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-10-16/monaco-murders-reveal-six-hidden-real-estate-billionaires.html Monaco Murders Reveal Six Hidden Real Estate Billionaires], ''Bloomberg'', October 18, 2014</ref><ref>Olivier Toscer, [http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/societe/20140521.OBS7894/helene-pastor-les-secrets-de-famille-de-la-vice-princesse-de-monaco.html Hélène Pastor : les secrets de famille de la "vice-princesse" de Monaco], ''[[Le Nouvel Observateur]]'', May 21, 2014</ref>
The building is mostly residential.<ref name="emporislebahia"/> However, it is also home to some shops.<ref name="emporislebahia"/>
