{{Infobox military conflict | conflict = Operation Echo | width = | partof = the [[Kosovo War]] | image = CF-18 Aviano Italy.jpg | caption = [[CF-18 Hornet]] departs Aviano Air Base, Italy | date = 1999 | place = Kosovo, Yugoslavia | coordinates = | map_type = | map_relief = | latitude = | longitude = | map_size = | map_marksize = | map_caption = | map_label = | territory = | result = Canadian success | status = | combatants_header = | combatant1 = {{flag|Canada}} | combatant2 = {{flag|FR Yugoslavia|name=Yugoslavia}} | combatant3 = | commander1 = [[Jean Chrétien]] | commander2 = [[Slobodan Milošević]] | commander3 = | units1 = {{air force|Canada|name=Air Command}} | units2 = [[Armed Forces of Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslav Armed Forces]] | units3 = | strength1 = | strength2 = | strength3 = | casualties1 = | casualties2 = | casualties3 = | notes = | campaignbox = }} '''Operation Echo''' was the codename given by the [[Canadian Forces]] for its air activities during the [[Kosovo War]] in 1999. In support of the NATO [[Operation Allied Force]] Canadian aircraft based at [[Aviano Air Base]] in northeastern Italy [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia|flew bombing missions]] over the Balkans.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.cmp-cpm.forces.gc.ca/dhh-dhp/od-bdo/di-ri-eng.asp?IntlOpId=96&CdnOpId=110 |title=Details/Information for Canadian Forces (CF) Operation Kinetic |work=CMP Directorate of History and Heritage|year=2013 |accessdate=11 September 2013}}</ref>
During the campaign the Canadian air contingent consisted of 18 [[McDonnell Douglas CF-18 Hornet|CF-18 Hornet]] aircraft from [[441 Tactical Fighter Squadron|441]] and [[425 Tactical Fighter Squadron]]s, with 69 aircrew and 250 ground crew. Between March 24 and June 10, 1999, they flew 684 [[sortie]]s in 224 missions, and dropped nearly {{Convert|500,000|lb|kg|abbr=on}} of gravity and precision-guided bombs. Despite the fact that they comprised less than 2% of the nearly 1,000 Allied aircraft engaged in the conflict, they flew on 10% of all bombing missions.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.cdfai.org/bergenarticles/New%20historic%20Battle%20Honour%20for%20Canadian%20jet%20fighter%20squadrons%20bittersweet.pdf |title=New historic Battle Honour for Canadian jet fighter squadrons bittersweet |first=Bob |last=Bergen |work=Canadian Defence & Foreign Affairs Institute |year=2013 |accessdate=11 September 2013}}</ref>
