In the [[mythology]] of the [[Africa]]n [[Songhai people]], '''Zin Kibaru''' or '''Zinkibaru''' is a blind, river-dwelling [[spiritual being|spirit]] who commands [[fish]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Stoller|first=Paul|date= 2010 |title=Fusion of the Worlds: An Ethnography of Possession Among the Songhay of Niger|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ncE8PvrxxHMC&pg=PA89|publisher=University of Chicago Press|page=89-90|isbn=9780226775494|access-date=4 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Coulter|first1=Charles Russell|last2=Turner|first2=Patricia|date=2013|title=Encyclopedia of Ancient Deities|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sEIngqiKOugC&pg=PA523|publisher=Routledge|page=523|isbn=9781135963903|access-date=4 February 2017}}</ref>
